spade /speɪd/

(spades) 

1. N-COUNT A spade is a tool used for digging, with a flat metal blade and a long handle. 锹 

例： ...a garden spade. …一把花园里使用的锹。 

2. N-UNCOUNT-COLL Spades is one of the four suits in a deck of playing cards. Each card in the suit is marked with one or more black symbols: ♠. (扑克牌中的) 黑桃 

例： ...the ace of spades. …黑桃A。 

3. N-COUNT A spade is a playing card of this suit. 黑桃牌 

例： He would have done better to play a spade now. 他要是现在出一张黑桃牌就更好了。 

4. V to use a spade on 用锹

